## Status: Sprint 13 CLOSED — v1.0.0-rc.1 · Gumtree infeasible; UX fixes shipped

### Sprint 13 (2026-03-21) — Gumtree Spike + UX Fixes

## Gumtree Spike

**Verdict: INFEASIBLE — sprint closed.**

Feasibility checked 2026-03-21 against `https://www.gumtree.com/robots.txt`.

**Key findings:**
- `robots.txt` contains `Disallow: /*?` — blocks **all** parameterized URLs including every make/model/price search query the pipeline uses.
- Without query params, Gumtree's browse path returns location-specific pages with no price filtering and no pagination.
- Page 1 of a national browse returned ~26 listings (70 total) but all at fixed location with no make/model narrowing — yield for a targeted arbitrage run would be <10 relevant listings.
- No embedded `__NEXT_DATA__` JSON; uses `window.gumtreeDataLayer` which requires JS rendering.
- Likely Cloudflare protection — static requests tier would yield sparse results even if robots.txt were satisfied.

**Conclusion:** Implementing a compliant Gumtree adapter would require either (a) violating `robots.txt` on parameterized search, or (b) accepting a non-filtered national browse yielding unacceptably low volume for the arbitrage use-case. Sprint acceptance criteria: "If not viable — document why and close sprint." Closing as non-viable.

**Next best alternative:** AutoTrader UK (`autotrader.co.uk`) — already partly wired as a comps source. A full AutoTrader search adapter may be viable (public search results, structured JSON, high UK car volume). Candidate for Sprint 14.

